node.text:
View at Paragliding World Cup 2021 🪂  Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on worlderlust.com (link in my bio: @worlderlust)

The Paragliding World Cup is a cross country flying competition for paraglider pilots, organized by the Paragliding World Cup Association, based in Marlens, France. Each year, the Paragliding World Cup Tour visits 5-6 different locations worldwide.

Is paragliding a sport you ever thought of trying? 🙌🏼

📽 @marcellauchoa
📍 Kopaonik, Serbia
🎶 SHAED - Trampoline (Jauz Remix)

2) European Starling - @raheel.aazim

5) Strawberry Finch - @praharsha_wildlife_stories

7) European Bee-eater - @dorugroza
8) Pink Robin - @ravi_arora
9) Keel billed Toucan - @floriankusterwildlife
10) Oriental Dwarf Kingfisher - @rahul_belsare

Rainbow Island, Iran 🇮🇷 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @worlderlust

The soil composing Hormuz Island in #Iran is highly concentrated with Iron Oxide. This concentration leads to red coloration, which is washed up in the waves.
Have you ever seen anything like this?

📽 @elhamgholami
📍 Hormuz, Iran
